        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2065365815" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7547804464949030848">Inspired by Stanley, in 2004 journalist Tim Butcher decided to retrace his steps and follow the River Congo through the heart of Africa. The resulting book is part travelogue, part history, and completely riveting. Along the way he meets some fascinating people and has some quite scary adventures (Mr Butcher is clearly a lot braver than I am!!). He also writes about the Congo’s history, and how its violent colonial past has impacted on its present state: corruption, lawlessness, poverty, a count</span>
  <span id="freeText7547804464949030848" style="display:none">Inspired by Stanley, in 2004 journalist Tim Butcher decided to retrace his steps and follow the River Congo through the heart of Africa. The resulting book is part travelogue, part history, and completely riveting. Along the way he meets some fascinating people and has some quite scary adventures (Mr Butcher is clearly a lot braver than I am!!). He also writes about the Congo’s history, and how its violent colonial past has impacted on its present state: corruption, lawlessness, poverty, a country which seems to have gone backwards as the rest of the world has developed. Fantastic story, fantastic book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7547804464949030848" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

